The paper deals with the problem of quantization of frame coefficients of signals, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of random frames with sub-Gaussian rows is a common technique in compressed sensing (cs.LG), and the paper extends the analysis to this setting. The paper also uses numerical methods to observe decay rates, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
